rComments: She is so sweet and caring and you can tell she wants her students to succeed! Despite it being an online course, she designed it to feel like an in-person class setting. She goes into a lot of detail during her lectures so make sure you're listening and taking notes!

One of the best professors I've had! She's really passionate about the subjects at hand so it makes lectures interesting to listen to. You can also tell she wants all her students to succeed so she reads as a very compassionate, lovely person. She focuses more on critical thinking rather than memorizing material to get good grades.
Had her into her first semester into teaching at @ uOttawa. Lovely lady who wants to see all of her students succeed.

She's a great professor. Very enthusiastic and she is fair in her grading. The topics she talks about are interesting so you will never be bored. I highly recommend her for SOC. PLUS it's individual and no group work.

Amazing professor! You had to have done the readings to be able to participate, but even if you were busy and didn't, she explained clearly enough that you could still grasp the concepts. The readings weren't long, about 30 mins to 1h per lecture, and they were easy. She is very nice too! The course was fun and easy marks. 100% recommend her.

The work load was reasonable and the tests pretty much reflected what she talks about in class. However, she's very condescending to students. She is also highly dependent on class participation for lectures. When students haven't done the readings or aren't participating she will bash the class rather than just continuing with the lecture

Loved professor Bronson! She's very sweet and really cares about you. She's really passionate about what she lectures and spends a lot of time explaining what she's expecting from assignments. I definitely recommend her classes! She's a great prof.

Ms. Bronson gives lots of work to do with the thought that it will help with knowing the material, but in fact it gives added pressure as the class takes up all your time. Little time to juggle and be efficient in all your classes because of that. You need to participate 10% do a presentation of the readings 15% have a midterm and written final
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Lots of homework']
